---
import Marketing from '../layouts/Marketing.astro';
import Container from '../components/Container.astro';

const lastUpdated = '12 April 2024';
---

<Marketing
  title="AcmePay | Terms of service"
  description="Read the AcmePay Terms of Service covering account responsibilities, acceptable use, pricing, and legal commitments for our payments platform."
>
  <section class="relative isolate overflow-hidden py-24">
    <div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 -z-10 bg-gradient-to-b from-purple-500/10 via-transparent to-transparent blur-3xl"></div>
    <Container>
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.45em] text-white/40">Legal</p>
        <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight md:text-5xl">Terms of service</h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-white/70">
          These terms govern your access to and use of AcmePay. They ensure we deliver a reliable platform while protecting your business and end customers.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-6 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-white/40">Last updated {lastUpdated}</p>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>

  <section class="pb-24">
    <Container>
      <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-10 text-sm leading-relaxed text-white/70">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">1. Acceptance of terms</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">By registering for or using AcmePay, you agree to these Terms of Service and all incorporated policies. If you use AcmePay on behalf of an organisation, you confirm you have authority to bind that organisation.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">2. Account requirements</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">You are responsible for maintaining accurate account information, safeguarding credentials, and ensuring your team follows applicable laws. We may request additional documentation to verify compliance obligations or risk posture.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">3. Fees and settlement</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">Pricing is outlined on our <a class="underline decoration-indigo-400/60 underline-offset-4" href="/pricing">pricing page</a> or in your order form. Fees are netted from processed transactions or invoiced monthly. Disputed amounts must be raised within 15 days of invoice receipt.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">4. Acceptable use</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">You may not use AcmePay for unlawful activities, high-risk categories prohibited by card networks, or to process payments on behalf of unauthorised third parties. We reserve the right to suspend accounts that violate network rules or pose security risk.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">5. Intellectual property</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">AcmePay retains all rights to the platform, APIs, and documentation. You grant us a limited licence to use your marks for customer lists and implementation guidance, subject to your brand guidelines.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">6. Termination</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">Either party may terminate with 30 days' notice. We may terminate immediately if you breach these terms, violate law, or create undue risk. Upon termination we will assist with data export and final settlement in a commercially reasonable timeframe.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">7. Disclaimers and liability</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">AcmePay is provided "as is" without warranties beyond those expressly stated. Neither party is liable for indirect or consequential damages. Our aggregate liability is limited to fees paid in the 12 months preceding the claim.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">8. Governing law</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">These terms are governed by the laws of the State of Delaware, excluding conflict-of-law principles. Disputes will be resolved in the state or federal courts located in New York County, NY, unless otherwise agreed in writing.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">9. Contact</h2>
          <p class="mt-3">Questions about these terms can be sent to <a class="underline decoration-indigo-400/60 underline-offset-4" href="mailto:legal@acmepay.com">legal@acmepay.com</a>. We will notify you of material updates via email or in-app messaging.</p>
        </section>
      </article>
    </Container>
  </section>
</Marketing>
